Code review came back. Spec compliance ✅. Code quality flagged 2 Important + 3 Minor issues. Ship the small fixes; defer the bigger refactors.

## Fix now (one focused follow-up commit)

### A. Add direct `storage:list-prefix` tests in BOTH storage packages

The plan landed `storage:list-prefix` as new infrastructure with a security-relevant LIKE-escape branch (`%`, `_`, `\\`), but the escape branch has no direct test in the storage package. CLAUDE.md "Bug Fix Policy" + "Half-Wired Code Policy" both want a test.

In `packages/storage-sqlite/src/__tests__/plugin.test.ts` (and equivalent in `packages/storage-postgres/src/__tests__/plugin.test.ts`), add:

```ts
describe('storage:list-prefix', () => {
  it('returns rows whose key starts with the literal prefix', async () => {
    // Seed: storage:set keys 'credential:v2:user:alice:foo', 'credential:v2:user:alice:bar', 'other:row'
    // List with prefix 'credential:v2:user:alice:'
    // Expect both alice rows; not 'other:row'
  });

  it('escapes SQL LIKE metacharacters in the prefix', async () => {
    // Seed two keys: 'credential:weird_user:r' and 'credential:weirdXuser:r'
    // List with prefix 'credential:weird_' (literal underscore)
    // Expect ONLY 'credential:weird_user:r' — not 'weirdXuser' (which would match if escape failed)
  });

  it('escapes percent in the prefix', async () => {
    // Similar: seed 'credential:50%off:k' and 'credential:50anything:k'; prefix 'credential:50%'
    // Expect only the literal-percent row.
  });

  it('rejects empty/missing prefix with invalid-payload', async () => {
    await expect(bus.call('storage:list-prefix', ctx, { prefix: '' })).rejects.toMatchObject({ code: 'invalid-payload' });
  });
});
```

For the postgres test: only add it if there's an existing pattern for in-memory or testcontainer-based postgres tests in that package. If postgres tests require a live database that the test env doesn't provide, add a `it.skip` placeholder with a comment pointing to the manual-test path. Don't invent new test infrastructure.

### B. Reject `ownerId` without `scope` in `credentials:list`

In `packages/credentials/src/plugin.ts` `credentials:list` handler — currently silently ignores `ownerId` when `scope` is undefined. Tighten:

```ts
if (input.scope === undefined && input.ownerId !== undefined) {
  throw new PluginError({
    code: 'invalid-payload',
    plugin: PLUGIN_NAME,
    message: 'ownerId filter requires scope to be specified',
  });
}
```

Add a test in `list.test.ts` asserting the rejection.

### C. Drop the vestigial `userId:` field from CLI `credentials:set` calls

`packages/cli/src/commands/credentials.ts` lines ~140 and ~297 — drop `userId: CLI_USER_ID` from the `credentials:set` calls. The facade's `CredentialsSetInput` only takes `scope`/`ownerId`/`ref`/`kind`/`payload`/...; the extra `userId:` is silently ignored and confusing.

The matching `credentials:get` call (which DOES take `userId`) stays as-is.

### Verify and commit

Run:
```
pnpm test --filter @ax/storage-sqlite --filter @ax/storage-postgres --filter @ax/credentials --filter @ax/cli
pnpm build
```

Both must pass.

Commit (all three fixes in one commit since they're all small):
```
git add packages/storage-sqlite packages/storage-postgres packages/credentials packages/cli
git commit -m "fix(credentials,storage): direct list-prefix tests; reject ownerId-without-scope; drop vestigial userId in CLI set"
```

## Defer (do NOT touch this PR)

- **Mutex narrowness under cross-user precedence** (reviewer Issue #1, Important): the inflight mutex keys on `(userId, ref)` but with the new precedence chain, two users hitting the same global OAuth credential each get their own slot — Phase 3 will care, Phase 1 doesn't (no OAuth refresh at non-user scopes yet). Add a one-line note to your final report so I can capture it as a Phase 3 prerequisite. Don't fix it now — Phase 3's design touches OAuth refresh paths anyway, the fix lands cleanly there.
- **`credentials/src/plugin.ts` size split** (reviewer Issue #3, Minor): defer to Phase 2 (Phase 2 will add HTTP route files; the natural split — `envelope.ts` / `validators.ts` / `resolution.ts` — happens organically when Phase 2 needs to import the validators).

## Final report

Just confirm:
- Test counts before/after for each affected package
- The commit SHA
- One line: "Phase 3 mutex prerequisite captured: <description>" — for my notes

